<figureCitation id="BCF82A73FFB167315987CDE98CA026CE" box="[677,761,1156,1183]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1426,1451]" captionTargetBox="[175,1411,186,1400]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[164,1423,181,1401]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Specimens of Ernsta and Agyllia. Dorsal and ventral views are on the left and right, respectively. DNA sample IDs are given, other data are in the Tab. S1: a. Ernsta colotes the type species of the genus Ernsta gen. n., NVG-18054F06; b. Ernsta delagoae, the type species of the subgenus Delaga subgen. n., NVG-18054F08; c. Agyllia agylla, the type species of the genus Agyllia gen. n., NVG-19039F03." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3697558" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3697558/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
